1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
https://slama.dev/comeback/

2
00:00:07,350 --> 00:00:12,050
Ivuska, you won't believe what happened to me.

3
00:00:12,110 --> 00:00:13,290
Did your kefir ferment?

4
00:00:13,890 --> 00:00:14,910
Don't be silly.

5
00:00:15,550 --> 00:00:16,050
Sorry.

6
00:00:16,450 --> 00:00:21,950
Hey, you don't even remember Kvetos from the flea market, do you?

7
00:00:22,050 --> 00:00:23,490
Kvetos from the flea market?

8
00:00:24,510 --> 00:00:25,150
A crook.

9
00:00:26,050 --> 00:00:27,270
Is that who you got this drunk with?

10
00:00:27,270 --> 00:00:28,830
I thought you weren't talking to him.

11
00:00:29,050 --> 00:00:30,670
I'm not, normally.

12
00:00:31,450 --> 00:00:33,950
But today I had a good time.

13
00:00:34,860 --> 00:00:35,400
I can see that.

14
00:00:35,540 --> 00:00:38,020
He kept bragging like crazy.

15
00:00:38,220 --> 00:00:40,920
But I showed him.

16
00:00:41,800 --> 00:00:43,600
I hope you weren't bragging too.

17
00:00:43,860 --> 00:00:44,920
I had to.

18
00:00:45,100 --> 00:00:48,200
I couldn't exactly tell him the truth, that wouldn't work.

19
00:00:48,340 --> 00:00:48,820
Dad.

20
00:00:48,820 --> 00:00:57,320
Ivuska, he keeps showing off that he has the biggest construction company in the district and that Ruzena is the deputy mayor.

21
00:00:57,320 --> 00:00:57,860
Ruzena?

22
00:00:57,860 --> 00:00:59,750
Didn't she go to a special school?

23
00:00:59,780 --> 00:01:00,400
Exactly.

24
00:01:00,400 --> 00:01:03,950
So I just had to tell him.

25
00:01:04,950 --> 00:01:06,050
And what exactly?

26
00:01:08,350 --> 00:01:11,750
That I'm the director of Metrostav.

27
00:01:11,950 --> 00:01:15,650
And Ozzak is a notary.

28
00:01:18,950 --> 00:01:20,750
And I lost my phone.

29
00:01:56,950 --> 00:01:58,140
Maria, this is a mess.

30
00:01:58,550 --> 00:01:59,460
Turn that off.

31
00:01:59,460 --> 00:02:01,650
What is it?

32
00:02:02,050 --> 00:02:03,250
Something for nausea.

33
00:02:03,250 --> 00:02:04,030
Ozzak's recipe.

34
00:02:05,150 --> 00:02:06,110
And what's in it?

35
00:02:06,450 --> 00:02:09,150
If I told you, it would work the other way.

36
00:02:15,450 --> 00:02:16,030
Yuck!

37
00:02:17,750 --> 00:02:19,350
I'd rather make some tea.

38
00:02:19,880 --> 00:02:20,600
What about the phone?

39
00:02:21,550 --> 00:02:23,050
That's the least of my worries.

40
00:02:23,750 --> 00:02:25,750
Oh God, I'm an idiot.

41
00:02:26,050 --> 00:02:27,650
I promised him we'd come.

42
00:02:27,950 --> 00:02:29,550
He said he'd slaughter a pig.

43
00:02:29,950 --> 00:02:30,550
Great.

44
00:02:30,850 --> 00:02:33,100
I've been wanting Ruzena's recipe for black cake anyway.

45
00:02:33,150 --> 00:02:34,650
Are you crazy?

46
00:02:34,750 --> 00:02:36,480
How can we go after what I told him?

47
00:02:36,480 --> 00:02:37,560
Well then we just won't go.

48
00:02:38,050 --> 00:02:39,100
That won't work either.

49
00:02:39,250 --> 00:02:40,550
He'd say I'm scared of him.

50
00:02:40,700 --> 00:02:42,300
I don't know what you two have against each other.

51
00:02:42,600 --> 00:02:44,620
I just can't stand how he's always showing off.

52
00:02:44,780 --> 00:02:45,980
Like you don't do that.

53
00:02:46,450 --> 00:02:48,950
But I'm glad you at least left me out of it.

54
00:02:51,550 --> 00:02:52,750
You didn't?

55
00:02:54,460 --> 00:02:55,620
You dance flamenco.

56
00:02:55,900 --> 00:02:56,460
Competitively.

57
00:02:57,710 --> 00:02:58,270
Sorry.

58
00:02:59,650 --> 00:03:03,950
When he was showing me photos of little Kvetos at dance school, I couldn't help myself.

59
00:03:04,150 --> 00:03:04,850
Wonderful.

60
00:03:05,250 --> 00:03:08,950
So I'll grab castanets, Ozzak will get glasses, and we'll head to Volary.

61
00:03:09,350 --> 00:03:10,050
By metro.

62
00:03:10,150 --> 00:03:11,250
Cut it out.

63
00:03:11,550 --> 00:03:12,950
Sarcasm won't help us.

64
00:03:14,260 --> 00:03:14,820
Wait.

65
00:03:16,250 --> 00:03:17,050
I don't have my phone.

66
00:03:18,450 --> 00:03:23,150
Kvetos won't be able to reach me, he'll get offended, and we won't have to go to the pig slaughter.

67
00:03:26,050 --> 00:03:27,350
We're going to the pig slaughter!

68
00:03:30,150 --> 00:03:31,650
How do you know about the pig slaughter?

69
00:03:32,550 --> 00:03:33,220
Kvetos called.

70
00:03:33,450 --> 00:03:34,850
You left your phone at my place.

71
00:03:34,950 --> 00:03:41,750
This is bad, hey, Kvetos told me to my face that I'm a notary.

72
00:03:42,380 --> 00:03:43,060
So what?

73
00:03:43,760 --> 00:03:44,740
I just went along with it.

74
00:03:44,900 --> 00:03:46,100
Everyone thinks that about you anyway, right?

75
00:04:02,580 --> 00:04:03,440
What is this?

76
00:04:03,950 --> 00:04:04,550
Tea.

77
00:04:04,950 --> 00:04:05,850
Linden.

78
00:04:06,250 --> 00:04:07,250
You wanted it.

79
00:04:07,650 --> 00:04:09,850
It's disgustingly sweet.

80
00:04:10,250 --> 00:04:12,150
Maybe I put too much linden in?

81
00:04:14,150 --> 00:04:15,650
I'll just have water.

82
00:04:17,350 --> 00:04:18,450
It's business.

83
00:04:21,450 --> 00:04:22,460
Get out of here!

84
00:04:22,460 --> 00:04:24,580
For God's sake, you stink.

85
00:04:24,760 --> 00:04:25,700
It's for the blood sausage soup.

86
00:04:27,950 --> 00:04:29,150
I couldn't get one anywhere.

87
00:04:29,550 --> 00:04:32,650
In the end, young Coufal and his buddies hauled it from work for a bottle.

88
00:04:33,850 --> 00:04:36,450
From work? He's only seven!

89
00:04:38,250 --> 00:04:39,550
Good thing they only gave him wine.

90
00:04:39,550 --> 00:04:41,480
And where are you returning it?

91
00:04:41,660 --> 00:04:42,540
Blood sausage soup, he said.

92
00:04:42,820 --> 00:04:44,300
Yeah, we're going to our cousin's for a pig slaughter.

93
00:04:44,640 --> 00:04:45,120
We're not going.

94
00:04:46,450 --> 00:04:48,440
I don't get it, why don't you want to go to the pig slaughter?

95
00:04:48,440 --> 00:04:49,180
It's complicated.

96
00:04:50,050 --> 00:04:51,050
It's simple.

97
00:04:51,420 --> 00:04:54,380
He told his cousin we're some fancy family and now he's afraid they'll find us out.

98
00:04:54,960 --> 00:04:56,120
Don't worry, bro, we can pull it off.

99
00:04:56,340 --> 00:04:59,220
And you think anyone's going to believe you're a notary?

100
00:05:00,100 --> 00:05:04,180
Oh well, I'll just drink a bit more than usual and then start screaming that I see white mice.

101
00:05:05,550 --> 00:05:06,550
Don't be daft.

102
00:05:06,750 --> 00:05:09,650
Sausages don't just lie around on the street.

103
00:05:10,350 --> 00:05:13,250
Well, I once found one like that.

104
00:05:14,050 --> 00:05:15,850
It could be a terrible embarrassment.

105
00:05:16,060 --> 00:05:16,800
What embarrassment?

106
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:17,880
When I rinsed it off.

107
00:05:19,450 --> 00:05:22,850
You can't cheat your family just because you can't bluff a little.

108
00:05:23,220 --> 00:05:24,200
I'm not cheating and I'm not bluffing.

109
00:05:24,360 --> 00:05:25,600
I should have stood up to my brother.

110
00:05:25,740 --> 00:05:26,580
Come on, tell me how it tastes.

111
00:05:26,880 --> 00:05:27,620
Ozzak, cut it out.

112
00:05:28,050 --> 00:05:29,650
You know he can't lie.

113
00:05:30,050 --> 00:05:30,550
Well, Kvetos, you'd actually bluff pretty well.

114
00:05:32,520 --> 00:05:32,940
Director.

115
00:05:34,200 --> 00:05:37,460
Look, take that pot and go return it to those kids.

116
00:05:38,050 --> 00:05:38,820
Now?

117
00:05:39,150 --> 00:05:40,040
Do you know how heavy it is?

118
00:05:40,350 --> 00:05:41,850
It's still full of tea.

119
00:05:45,250 --> 00:05:47,930
If you're not up for it, I could help you out.

120
00:05:48,250 --> 00:05:49,130
How exactly?

121
00:05:49,450 --> 00:05:51,050
I could maybe go with you guys.

122
00:05:51,250 --> 00:05:52,230
As your spokesperson.

123
00:05:52,550 --> 00:05:54,990
You wouldn't have to lie and I'd say everything for you.

124
00:05:54,990 --> 00:05:55,550
Director.

125
00:05:57,550 --> 00:06:02,440
Pepita, listen, you can't come along as a spokesperson, that's completely absurd.

126
00:06:02,440 --> 00:06:04,500
What's absurd is not getting anything from relatives.

127
00:06:08,350 --> 00:06:09,050
Hi.

128
00:06:10,060 --> 00:06:10,920
Hi, mom.

129
00:06:11,850 --> 00:06:14,650
What did great-aunt send me?

130
00:06:18,010 --> 00:06:18,570
Nothing?

131
00:06:18,570 --> 00:06:21,750
She said she's not falling for these tricks anymore.

132
00:06:22,450 --> 00:06:32,550
What's wrong?

133
00:06:35,850 --> 00:06:37,850
Ivo, can we leave a Fidorka bar at your place?

134
00:06:38,150 --> 00:06:39,050
A Fidorka bar?

135
00:06:39,950 --> 00:06:40,650
Why?

136
00:06:41,350 --> 00:06:42,650
We got it from great-aunt.

137
00:06:43,360 --> 00:06:44,300
I'm sorry, what?

138
00:06:44,620 --> 00:06:47,620
We agreed that whoever goes the longest without saying one letter gets to eat it.

139
00:06:47,780 --> 00:06:50,240
And if we kept it at home, someone would eat it at night.

140
00:06:50,780 --> 00:06:51,640
How dare you.

141
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:52,980
I'm hungry, man.

142
00:06:53,450 --> 00:06:55,750
Yeah, last time you ate my pear.

143
00:06:57,020 --> 00:06:57,400
Oh God.

144
00:06:58,350 --> 00:07:00,250
Ivo, do you know which letter it is?

145
00:07:00,760 --> 00:07:01,140
I think so.

146
00:07:01,140 --> 00:07:02,750
Well, great then.

147
00:07:03,310 --> 00:07:03,690
R?

148
00:07:04,210 --> 00:07:04,590
Yeah.

149
00:07:06,850 --> 00:07:08,550
What if I gave you another Fidorka bar?

150
00:07:08,650 --> 00:07:09,950
Would you stop this?

151
00:07:10,750 --> 00:07:14,450
Great-aunt deliberately gave us just one to spark our competitiveness.

152
00:07:15,650 --> 00:07:16,650
Great idea, huh?

153
00:07:17,850 --> 00:07:18,950
Grumbling's not allowed either.

154
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:20,940
I don't want to risk it.

155
00:07:22,750 --> 00:07:23,560
I'd like to see that.

156
00:07:23,850 --> 00:07:27,650
When the teacher quizzes you tomorrow on the French Revolution.

157
00:07:27,680 --> 00:07:28,920
Damn it.

158
00:07:32,560 --> 00:07:39,060
It's morning.

159
00:07:42,450 --> 00:07:43,450
Where did this come from?

160
00:07:44,250 --> 00:07:45,550
Ozzak left it for you.

161
00:07:46,350 --> 00:07:47,550
So you'd know.

162
00:07:48,950 --> 00:07:53,450
He really thinks that if he hangs a pig here, I'll go to the pig slaughter.

163
00:07:54,150 --> 00:07:58,450
In that case, I don't understand why he tore down my poster of Tri Clunky yesterday.

164
00:07:59,350 --> 00:08:00,550
He hates Nohavica.

165
00:08:04,950 --> 00:08:05,450
Hello?

166
00:08:06,850 --> 00:08:08,250
Yes, I'll pass you over.

167
00:08:10,350 --> 00:08:11,250
Pacovsky!

168
00:08:12,700 --> 00:08:13,680
Hey, Kvetos.

169
00:08:15,350 --> 00:08:18,550
Well, how do you think I feel, you know, we had a few drinks yesterday.

170
00:08:20,050 --> 00:08:22,450
Well, I went for a run this morning too, of course.

171
00:08:23,840 --> 00:08:24,360
How far?

172
00:08:24,360 --> 00:08:25,850
Only five kilometers, right?

173
00:08:26,150 --> 00:08:28,050
Well, there you go, it'll get even better.

174
00:08:28,950 --> 00:08:29,850
What woman?

175
00:08:31,150 --> 00:08:35,350
Oh, the phone's answered by my... secretary.

176
00:08:36,950 --> 00:08:39,450
Well, you know, I wouldn't pick an ugly one.

177
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:41,560
Taking it easy?

178
00:08:41,560 --> 00:08:45,460
No way, you know, the metro doesn't build itself.

179
00:08:45,460 --> 00:08:47,840
Yeah, hold on.

180
00:08:47,840 --> 00:08:53,190
Xenie, stop standing around and take those invoices to accounting.

181
00:08:53,650 --> 00:08:56,350
Chop, chop, chop, chop, get out of my sight.

182
00:09:00,550 --> 00:09:03,650
Damn secretaries, they never do anything.

183
00:09:04,250 --> 00:09:05,550
You have a secretary too?

184
00:09:06,250 --> 00:09:08,350
Be glad you don't, she's nothing special.

185
00:09:09,390 --> 00:09:10,290
And how's Ruzena?

186
00:09:12,350 --> 00:09:13,550
She's heading to parliament.

187
00:09:14,150 --> 00:09:17,050
Well of course, who else should be there but her?

188
00:09:17,740 --> 00:09:20,380
Yeah, Kvetos, listen, about the pig slaughter.

189
00:09:20,380 --> 00:09:24,100
Look, I'm completely booked until June, completely, you know, and...

190
00:09:25,650 --> 00:09:28,040
No, of course I'm not bragging.

191
00:09:28,250 --> 00:09:30,460
I can take time off whenever I want.

192
00:09:30,460 --> 00:09:30,980
What?

193
00:09:30,980 --> 00:09:32,450
Saturday, sure, no problem.

194
00:09:32,600 --> 00:09:33,160
Sure.

195
00:09:33,750 --> 00:09:34,800
Yeah, all three of us.

196
00:09:34,800 --> 00:09:35,360
Hold on.

197
00:09:35,360 --> 00:09:37,550
Xenie, what am I doing on Saturday?

198
00:09:37,700 --> 00:09:39,280
Cancel the minister.

199
00:09:39,280 --> 00:09:41,420
Ruzena will fire him after the elections anyway.

200
00:09:41,750 --> 00:09:46,750
And call Iva and the doctor and tell them we're going to Volary on Saturday.

201
00:09:47,550 --> 00:09:49,020
Yeah, it's all set.

202
00:09:49,020 --> 00:09:50,180
I'm so looking forward to it.

203
00:09:50,180 --> 00:09:51,280
Builder's honor.

204
00:09:51,380 --> 00:09:52,040
See ya.

205
00:09:54,250 --> 00:09:55,050
Xenie.

206
00:09:56,750 --> 00:09:57,700
Jesus Christ.

207
00:10:00,150 --> 00:10:01,350
What just came over me?

208
00:10:02,550 --> 00:10:03,550
Oh, you men.

209
00:10:04,050 --> 00:10:07,280
You were lying just like Zoran when he calls his brother.

210
00:10:07,550 --> 00:10:10,220
The other day he even told him he bought an island.

211
00:10:10,220 --> 00:10:11,580
Well, that's really something.

212
00:10:11,700 --> 00:10:12,180
You know.

213
00:10:12,180 --> 00:10:15,050
Although it's really just a small island.

214
00:10:24,600 --> 00:10:25,160
Bye!

215
00:10:25,760 --> 00:10:26,320
Bye.

216
00:10:26,990 --> 00:10:27,550
Coffee.

217
00:10:31,650 --> 00:10:33,050
Well, thanks a lot.

218
00:10:33,950 --> 00:10:34,750
Sorry.

219
00:10:34,950 --> 00:10:37,150
I was kept after school for two hours and all you say is sorry?

220
00:10:38,850 --> 00:10:40,540
You know I'm not allowed to say that letter.

221
00:10:40,950 --> 00:10:42,650
Then don't help me at all.

222
00:10:43,930 --> 00:10:44,490
Sorry.

223
00:10:44,970 --> 00:10:46,290
Everyone was laughing at me.

224
00:10:47,150 --> 00:10:51,720
Because of you I said that the Jacobins "pampered" Louis the Sixteenth.

225
00:10:51,720 --> 00:10:52,240
Shut up.

226
00:10:53,250 --> 00:10:55,250
I didn't tell you to say "pampered."

227
00:10:55,750 --> 00:10:57,490
Because of your stupid game I got a failing grade.

228
00:10:57,850 --> 00:10:59,170
I got a failing grade too.

229
00:10:59,550 --> 00:11:00,350
But in math.

230
00:11:00,350 --> 00:11:02,110
Because you still don't know how to divide fractions.

231
00:11:02,330 --> 00:11:03,770
And you don't even know they executed him.

232
00:11:07,950 --> 00:11:09,350
You're still not ready?

233
00:11:10,450 --> 00:11:13,670
Mom, couldn't we just go to dad's normally today?

234
00:11:13,950 --> 00:11:18,350
When he starts paying child support properly, then for all I care you don't have to go at all.

235
00:11:22,910 --> 00:11:23,430
Ivo.

236
00:11:24,550 --> 00:11:26,580
So you're going to the pig slaughter after all.

237
00:11:26,650 --> 00:11:27,650
Dad maybe.

238
00:11:27,950 --> 00:11:28,620
Not Ozzak?

239
00:11:28,950 --> 00:11:30,250
He's been getting sick from grass.

240
00:11:30,550 --> 00:11:32,240
He thinks it'll clean out his stomach.

241
00:11:32,750 --> 00:11:36,150
I want to see how they'll react to a notary who vomits daisies.

242
00:11:36,250 --> 00:11:38,740
Such a show over a bit of headcheese, right?

243
00:11:38,740 --> 00:11:39,180
Exactly.

244
00:11:40,350 --> 00:11:41,410
So you're not going?

245
00:11:41,650 --> 00:11:42,630
Am I crazy?

246
00:11:42,850 --> 00:11:45,110
Having to pretend I can do flamenco?

247
00:11:45,110 --> 00:11:45,550
Flamenco?

248
00:11:45,850 --> 00:11:46,210
Yeah.

249
00:11:47,050 --> 00:11:50,830
Oh, Ozzak told me you'd be playing the womanizer, that didn't make sense to me.

250
00:11:50,830 --> 00:11:52,630
Neither womanizer nor flamenco.

251
00:11:52,750 --> 00:11:53,470
I'm not going anywhere.

252
00:11:53,740 --> 00:11:54,180
You're right.

253
00:11:54,550 --> 00:11:57,150
One should maintain dignity in front of relatives.

254
00:11:57,860 --> 00:11:59,650
Ow, Sasa!

255
00:12:00,250 --> 00:12:01,370
He's revving up the car!

256
00:12:01,570 --> 00:12:03,410
Uncle Horvat drives me to social services.

257
00:12:05,250 --> 00:12:05,650
He says where's his office?

258
00:12:17,540 --> 00:12:18,840
I can't read your handwriting.

259
00:12:19,020 --> 00:12:19,740
On Celetna Street.

260
00:12:20,550 --> 00:12:21,400
Damn!

261
00:12:21,400 --> 00:12:21,780
What?

262
00:12:22,080 --> 00:12:23,800
That's not a proper pub!

263
00:12:24,800 --> 00:12:26,280
Jesus, does it really matter?

264
00:12:26,480 --> 00:12:27,280
It sure does!

265
00:12:27,850 --> 00:12:29,350
I may be a notary, but I'm not going to be a teetotaler because of it.

266
00:12:31,900 --> 00:12:32,780
But back to the point.

267
00:12:33,550 --> 00:12:35,150
What if I went there alone?

268
00:12:35,310 --> 00:12:36,170
Oh, come on...

269
00:12:35,970 --> 00:12:36,170
.

270
00:12:36,170 --> 00:12:37,510
You know, I've already eaten enough grass.

271
00:12:37,750 --> 00:12:39,190
And I'd bring you back sausages.

272
00:12:39,190 --> 00:12:39,990
What about the snout?

273
00:12:40,110 --> 00:12:41,690
You'd be lost there without me, right?

274
00:12:42,690 --> 00:12:43,610
Oh God, this is going to be a disaster.

275
00:12:44,550 --> 00:12:46,450
Easy, bro, we'll manage.

276
00:12:47,750 --> 00:12:49,450
Hey, we know how to work in disguise, right?

277
00:12:49,640 --> 00:12:50,000
Really?

278
00:12:51,750 --> 00:12:56,150
We didn't free Ivuska that time, but in those masks we made it right up to her.

279
00:12:56,450 --> 00:12:59,300
Yeah, you mean when we visited her in the hospital's infectious ward?

280
00:12:59,300 --> 00:12:59,580
Yeah!

281
00:13:16,550 --> 00:13:19,350
I promised I'd help you, and Iva doesn't want to go.

282
00:13:21,450 --> 00:13:23,330
You've completely lost your mind.

283
00:13:23,470 --> 00:13:24,390
Great, we'll manage.

284
00:13:24,610 --> 00:13:24,970
Dad.

285
00:13:26,030 --> 00:13:26,510
Out!

286
00:13:28,650 --> 00:13:30,620
Sorry, these clothes probably aren't good enough.

287
00:13:30,620 --> 00:13:31,300
Turn him away too.

288
00:13:31,640 --> 00:13:32,500
Now!

289
00:13:32,500 --> 00:13:35,550
You don't know what it's like at a performance at the National Theatre.

290
00:13:45,350 --> 00:13:47,750
We went to dad's and he didn't let us in.

291
00:13:49,150 --> 00:13:49,950
I'm the winner!

292
00:13:50,250 --> 00:13:51,070
Winner!

293
00:13:51,070 --> 00:13:52,230
Lexa, what do you mean winner?

294
00:13:52,270 --> 00:13:53,190
I didn't say it.

295
00:13:53,650 --> 00:13:54,130
Again?

296
00:13:54,450 --> 00:13:55,510
No, I said "that"?

297
00:13:55,590 --> 00:13:56,630
And that's not the letter.

298
00:13:56,890 --> 00:13:57,290
Yes it is.

299
00:13:57,950 --> 00:13:59,850
No, it isn't, "that" is allowed.

300
00:14:01,050 --> 00:14:01,450
Oh, great.

301
00:14:05,320 --> 00:14:06,160
Should I go then?

302
00:14:06,340 --> 00:14:07,140
No, Ivo, wait.

303
00:14:07,750 --> 00:14:09,360
We'll tell you what it was like there.

304
00:14:09,650 --> 00:14:11,400
Dad and his new wife bought a villa.

305
00:14:11,650 --> 00:14:12,780
They must have done well for themselves.

306
00:14:12,950 --> 00:14:15,250
Well, she breeds Great Danes.

307
00:14:15,980 --> 00:14:16,460
Purebreds.

308
00:14:18,550 --> 00:14:22,050
Really, she had lots of puppies and let me play with them.

309
00:14:22,950 --> 00:14:24,320
And the wife's okay?

310
00:14:24,650 --> 00:14:28,250
She bought us sundaes, but I didn't really like them.

311
00:14:28,700 --> 00:14:29,180
Sundaes?

312
00:14:29,180 --> 00:14:32,350
Auntie, a sundae, like ice cream.

313
00:14:32,540 --> 00:14:33,580
Oh right, a sundae.

314
00:14:33,680 --> 00:14:34,540
I like her.

315
00:14:35,450 --> 00:14:36,450
She wears nice snakes.

316
00:14:37,450 --> 00:14:38,250
Grass snakes.

317
00:14:38,550 --> 00:14:42,250
And she had a really great dog.

318
00:14:42,950 --> 00:14:44,350
I know, you already said that.

319
00:14:44,550 --> 00:14:45,750
No, that's not what I said.

320
00:14:46,050 --> 00:14:47,750
He meant, like, a pig.

321
00:14:48,350 --> 00:14:50,350
Oh, a pig.

322
00:14:51,270 --> 00:15:04,740
What happened?

323
00:15:06,750 --> 00:15:10,250
I'm such an idiot.

324
00:15:10,950 --> 00:15:11,650
Kvetos?

325
00:15:12,250 --> 00:15:13,760
Why does he keep calling me?

326
00:15:13,950 --> 00:15:14,950
What was he bragging about?

327
00:15:15,450 --> 00:15:16,200
How do you know?

328
00:15:16,350 --> 00:15:18,550
Zoran only calls when he's bought something new.

329
00:15:19,250 --> 00:15:21,150
He just bought a BMW, you know.

330
00:15:21,650 --> 00:15:23,150
Oh dear, and what about you?

331
00:15:23,250 --> 00:15:24,780
Luckily I didn't mention the brand.

332
00:15:25,050 --> 00:15:26,950
Just that my car is better.

333
00:15:28,450 --> 00:15:29,150
Marcelka, Zoran has several cars though.

334
00:15:31,340 --> 00:15:33,040
Could he lend me one for the weekend?

335
00:15:33,180 --> 00:15:34,300
Oh, you men.

336
00:15:34,850 --> 00:15:37,800
I don't know exactly how many cars we have at home right now.

337
00:15:38,250 --> 00:15:41,000
But there's one big one in the yard that we don't use much.

338
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:42,180
And what brand is it?

339
00:15:43,250 --> 00:15:43,950
I don't know.

340
00:15:44,650 --> 00:15:47,350
It sounded like some kind of shellfish.

341
00:15:48,350 --> 00:15:49,740
Renault Laguna?

342
00:15:49,950 --> 00:15:52,250
That must be it.

343
00:16:03,550 --> 00:16:04,850
You really overdid it.

344
00:16:05,450 --> 00:16:06,490
What are you talking about?

345
00:16:06,850 --> 00:16:07,890
Don't play dumb.

346
00:16:08,150 --> 00:16:09,030
Kvetos called me.

347
00:16:09,450 --> 00:16:10,330
What happened?

348
00:16:10,650 --> 00:16:11,650
What happened?

349
00:16:12,250 --> 00:16:18,050
Get this -- Kvetos complained that I never told him we have a cousin Simona in Prague.

350
00:16:18,450 --> 00:16:18,930
No way.

351
00:16:20,650 --> 00:16:27,550
She has two kids, she's very poor, and when Kvetos invited her to the pig slaughter, she said she can't come because she can't afford the train.

352
00:16:27,790 --> 00:16:28,870
Poor woman.

353
00:16:29,390 --> 00:16:31,570
You really think you're going to ride to Volary with me?

354
00:16:31,730 --> 00:16:32,910
Mooching off my relatives?

355
00:16:34,150 --> 00:16:35,450
I could hitchhike.

356
00:16:35,750 --> 00:16:39,250
But then don't expect me to say nice things about you, cousin.

357
00:16:41,950 --> 00:16:43,450
So what time do we leave tomorrow?

358
00:16:45,770 --> 00:16:46,550
Five.

359
00:16:49,050 --> 00:16:50,050
That's on me.

360
00:16:58,950 --> 00:16:59,850
I don't want to.

361
00:17:00,350 --> 00:17:02,260
No suit, no pig slaughter.

362
00:17:02,260 --> 00:17:03,260
But why?

363
00:17:03,650 --> 00:17:04,650
Because I said so.

364
00:17:05,450 --> 00:17:06,840
At least try it on.

365
00:17:07,150 --> 00:17:09,520
That's what you said about that nice piece of cloth for my neck too.

366
00:17:09,520 --> 00:17:10,500
At least try it on.

367
00:17:11,080 --> 00:17:12,380
Then I found out I was in the Young Pioneers.

368
00:17:12,480 --> 00:17:13,280
That was a different era.

369
00:17:13,460 --> 00:17:13,900
I don't want to!

370
00:17:15,150 --> 00:17:16,350
Fine, I'm calling Kvetos.

371
00:17:18,150 --> 00:17:19,150
Hi, Tomas speaking.

372
00:17:19,350 --> 00:17:22,230
Listen, bad news, the doctor won't make it after all.

373
00:17:22,450 --> 00:17:28,150
Some flu or something. Hey, no worries, more sausages for us.

374
00:17:28,550 --> 00:17:30,350
Sure, let's do it.

375
00:17:32,450 --> 00:17:33,650
I know you're not really calling him.

376
00:17:34,100 --> 00:17:35,760
Stop faking, it doesn't work on me.

377
00:17:35,860 --> 00:17:36,540
Give it here.

378
00:17:37,650 --> 00:17:38,450
Weasels.

379
00:17:43,450 --> 00:17:45,010
Alright, he's feeling a bit better.

380
00:17:45,010 --> 00:17:45,930
So tomorrow then.

381
00:17:47,750 --> 00:17:49,170
Yeah, we're bringing Simona.

382
00:17:49,310 --> 00:17:49,770
Bye.

383
00:18:01,350 --> 00:18:02,610
Where have you been so long?

384
00:18:02,750 --> 00:18:04,150
I was in the park.

385
00:18:04,320 --> 00:18:04,840
Where?

386
00:18:06,150 --> 00:18:07,150
In the park.

387
00:18:07,850 --> 00:18:12,580
I thought you said "in a trap."

388
00:18:13,050 --> 00:18:14,350
What's this supposed to be?

389
00:18:16,670 --> 00:18:17,190
A dress.

390
00:18:17,650 --> 00:18:18,250
I'm not going.

391
00:18:19,650 --> 00:18:20,950
At least try it on.

392
00:18:21,250 --> 00:18:24,050
You said that about braces too, and then I had to wear them for three years.

393
00:18:24,150 --> 00:18:25,710
And look how nice and straight your teeth are.

394
00:18:25,710 --> 00:18:26,050
I'm not going.

395
00:18:27,750 --> 00:18:29,620
Kvetos's wife Kveta will be tap dancing.

396
00:18:29,620 --> 00:18:29,700
No.

397
00:18:30,700 --> 00:18:31,940
Do it for me.

398
00:18:31,940 --> 00:18:35,450
I'm not going to make a fool of myself just because you and Kvetos keep trying to one-up each other.

399
00:18:36,150 --> 00:18:37,610
Ivuska, please.

400
00:18:37,610 --> 00:18:37,950
No.

401
00:18:40,550 --> 00:18:41,450
Ivo, come here.

402
00:18:45,250 --> 00:18:46,950
This is when Kvetos and I went fishing.

403
00:18:46,950 --> 00:18:47,690
We were seven.

404
00:18:51,350 --> 00:18:52,650
And who's got the bigger fish?

405
00:18:55,560 --> 00:18:56,560
He always had the upper hand.

406
00:18:56,760 --> 00:18:58,820
When I had a bike, he already had a moped.

407
00:18:58,880 --> 00:19:01,080
When I had a moped, he already had a Zhiguli.

408
00:19:03,050 --> 00:19:04,750
Here we went pony riding together.

409
00:19:05,650 --> 00:19:06,850
And who's riding the goat?

410
00:19:07,120 --> 00:19:07,560
You.

411
00:19:09,050 --> 00:19:09,650
See.

412
00:19:10,750 --> 00:19:12,650
Dad, I don't even know flamenco.

413
00:19:13,850 --> 00:19:15,750
You think those hicks will know the difference?

414
00:19:16,650 --> 00:19:16,990
Ivo.

415
00:19:16,990 --> 00:19:18,790
Oh, fine.

416
00:19:20,450 --> 00:19:21,650
But I'm keeping the dress.

417
00:19:24,110 --> 00:19:25,070
It was a Hummer!

418
00:19:26,090 --> 00:19:26,630
What?

419
00:19:26,630 --> 00:19:28,750
The car is called a Hummer.

420
00:19:28,750 --> 00:19:30,550
Are you holding a grenade?

421
00:19:30,550 --> 00:19:33,190
No, it's just a keychain.

422
00:19:33,190 --> 00:19:36,950
Zoran bought the car from some soldiers and this was already on it.

423
00:19:37,580 --> 00:19:38,780
So he'll lend it to me?

424
00:19:39,070 --> 00:19:40,230
He was in a good mood today.

425
00:19:40,250 --> 00:19:41,910
He finally has a bigger yacht than his brother.

426
00:19:42,690 --> 00:19:43,410
Marcelka, thank you.

427
00:19:43,530 --> 00:19:44,130
You're a treasure.

428
00:19:44,170 --> 00:19:46,070
Thank the Somali pirates.

429
00:19:47,450 --> 00:19:49,790
I thought you arranged the car for me.

430
00:19:50,050 --> 00:19:51,550
But only with a driver.

431
00:19:52,550 --> 00:19:54,490
Yeah, he'll give me a driver too.

432
00:19:54,490 --> 00:19:56,130
He wasn't in that good a mood.

433
00:19:56,190 --> 00:19:58,430
But I figured Xenie could come too.

434
00:19:59,470 --> 00:20:00,530
And who's that again?

435
00:20:02,370 --> 00:20:03,010
Oh, right.

436
00:20:03,840 --> 00:20:06,760
And is the Hummer bigger than the BMW? There'll be a lot of us.

437
00:20:06,760 --> 00:20:12,750
Zoran sometimes holds board meetings in it, so we'll all fit even if we leave the pool table in.

438
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:30,760
Hurry up!

439
00:20:31,350 --> 00:20:32,620
Marcelka's already here!

440
00:20:32,620 --> 00:20:33,020
One moment!

441
00:20:33,540 --> 00:20:35,560
Wait, you need to tie my tie!

442
00:20:35,620 --> 00:20:37,040
Jesus, stop fussing!

443
00:20:37,640 --> 00:20:38,040
Tie!

444
00:20:38,750 --> 00:20:39,950
A Corvette is a car!

445
00:20:40,720 --> 00:20:41,120
Chevrolet!

446
00:20:45,910 --> 00:20:48,410
I don't get why you couldn't just get dressed at home.

447
00:20:48,550 --> 00:20:50,330
Right, like I'd want someone to see me like this on the street.

448
00:20:50,750 --> 00:20:52,750
Who's going to see you at five in the morning?

449
00:20:52,800 --> 00:20:54,300
What time do you think the guys get back from the late-night bar?

450
00:21:02,070 --> 00:21:02,930
Does it suit you?

451
00:21:03,650 --> 00:21:04,950
She looks like a princess.

452
00:21:04,970 --> 00:21:05,530
Thank you.

453
00:21:06,650 --> 00:21:10,550
That green Opel out there, does it belong to someone from the building?

454
00:21:11,650 --> 00:21:16,050
Well, Ozzak, you actually look like a human being.

455
00:21:16,460 --> 00:21:17,460
It can be taken off.

456
00:21:17,560 --> 00:21:19,140
No suit, no pig slaughter.

457
00:21:20,950 --> 00:21:23,720
Pacovsky, you didn't crash into that Opel, did you?

458
00:21:23,720 --> 00:21:25,820
I didn't crash into it, more like drove over it.

459
00:21:25,820 --> 00:21:28,750
It's really hard to see down from the cabin.

460
00:21:29,050 --> 00:21:30,750
What's this?

461
00:21:32,350 --> 00:21:36,150
If there are any problems, you'll be called away for an inspection of the Blanka tunnel.

462
00:21:37,150 --> 00:21:39,450
Marcelka, you think of everything.

463
00:21:41,710 --> 00:21:42,290
Xenie.

464
00:21:48,590 --> 00:21:49,510
Hello, family.

465
00:21:52,130 --> 00:21:53,130
Hello, Simona.

466
00:21:53,290 --> 00:21:53,750
Simona?

467
00:21:54,350 --> 00:21:55,950
So you'll be the one dancing, huh?

468
00:21:57,720 --> 00:21:58,300
Smart.

469
00:22:02,950 --> 00:22:05,000
Wait, what's he doing here?

470
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:06,560
That's Simona's partner Julek.

471
00:22:07,440 --> 00:22:09,680
Poor guy, hasn't had a job in three years.

472
00:22:10,050 --> 00:22:12,050
Which happens to be true.

473
00:22:30,350 --> 00:22:32,150
Marcelka, can't we go faster?

474
00:22:32,450 --> 00:22:33,350
We can't.

475
00:22:34,050 --> 00:22:35,110
The four-wheel drive locked up.

476
00:22:35,450 --> 00:22:36,450
All by itself.

477
00:22:37,650 --> 00:22:39,450
I feel like we're driving across a field.

478
00:22:41,850 --> 00:22:43,050
We are driving across a field.

479
00:22:44,050 --> 00:22:46,650
It's really hard to see past the winch.

480
00:22:46,850 --> 00:22:48,520
I'll call him that we'll be late.

481
00:22:48,520 --> 00:22:50,840
I'm worried that if they butcher the pig without me, you'll pay for it.

482
00:22:50,960 --> 00:22:52,020
Like, with me it would...

483
00:22:54,150 --> 00:22:54,950
No answer.

484
00:22:56,650 --> 00:22:58,750
Hey, Kvetos, hi, so...

485
00:22:58,850 --> 00:23:01,870
Hope I didn't wake you, you old sleepyhead.

486
00:23:02,350 --> 00:23:05,150
Yeah, we're on our way, of course we're coming.

487
00:23:07,350 --> 00:23:08,850
What do you mean, just showing off?

488
00:23:10,150 --> 00:23:11,240
He can't be serious.

489
00:23:11,240 --> 00:23:11,400
What?

490
00:23:13,050 --> 00:23:16,120
Kvetos, I cancelled a meeting with a minister because of you.

491
00:23:16,450 --> 00:23:18,680
And Xenie here gave up her trip to the Canaries.

492
00:23:18,680 --> 00:23:19,860
And I took the Corvette!

493
00:23:21,950 --> 00:23:24,530
Kvetos, listen, you started it, right?

494
00:23:24,950 --> 00:23:26,230
You're like a little kid.

495
00:23:26,550 --> 00:23:28,450
Let me tell you something, listen.

496
00:23:28,550 --> 00:23:33,650
People who lie like that and always want to be the best really piss me off.

497
00:23:34,150 --> 00:23:35,390
You bet.

498
00:23:35,950 --> 00:23:38,790
And don't count on us ever coming.

499
00:23:38,790 --> 00:23:39,390
We're not coming.

500
00:23:40,150 --> 00:23:42,570
And I'm not voting for Ruzena.

501
00:23:42,570 --> 00:23:43,170
Nobody is.

502
00:23:43,430 --> 00:23:44,610
We're not voting for Ruzena.

503
00:23:44,690 --> 00:23:45,350
Nobody, got it?

504
00:23:46,050 --> 00:23:46,650
Nobody.

505
00:23:46,950 --> 00:23:47,750
Goodbye.

506
00:23:51,210 --> 00:23:52,870
So the pig slaughter is off.

507
00:23:52,930 --> 00:23:53,290
Now what?

508
00:23:53,410 --> 00:23:54,570
Just turning around.

509
00:23:55,150 --> 00:23:55,550
What kind of person are you, Director?

510
00:24:00,450 --> 00:24:01,330
What do you mean?

511
00:24:01,450 --> 00:24:02,850
Those people haven't eaten in two days.

512
00:24:03,450 --> 00:24:06,300
And I've been eating grass, bro!

513
00:24:06,950 --> 00:24:08,380
And Horvat lost his deposit!

514
00:24:08,380 --> 00:24:10,460
I was also supposed to have a minister!

515
00:24:10,480 --> 00:24:11,840
He went on vacation!

516
00:24:11,980 --> 00:24:13,120
And has an empty apartment!

517
00:24:13,450 --> 00:24:16,350
So what the hell am I supposed to do?

518
00:24:18,850 --> 00:24:21,350
What was that?

519
00:24:22,350 --> 00:24:23,850
We ran over something.

520
00:24:24,120 --> 00:24:25,040
Oh God, what?

521
00:24:25,380 --> 00:24:26,380
I don't know!

522
00:24:27,350 --> 00:24:28,250
All I can see is that damn winch!

523
00:24:30,340 --> 00:24:32,060
It looked like a wild boar!

524
00:24:36,550 --> 00:24:37,120
Brake!

525
00:24:37,120 --> 00:24:37,560
Brake!

526
00:24:38,020 --> 00:24:38,640
Now!

527
00:24:39,620 --> 00:24:40,060
Keep going!

528
00:24:41,050 --> 00:24:48,750
Is everyone okay?

529
00:24:49,990 --> 00:24:50,810
The snout is mine!

530
00:24:50,910 --> 00:24:51,470
It's mine!

531
00:25:07,350 --> 00:25:11,050
Pacovsky here, Kvetos, hi.

532
00:25:12,950 --> 00:25:14,550
Yeah yeah, we arrived safely.

533
00:25:15,950 --> 00:25:20,850
Working hard, working hard, you know, the metro line D doesn't build itself.

534
00:25:22,150 --> 00:25:24,250
Yeah, sure, we should get together sometime.

535
00:25:25,750 --> 00:25:28,140
Yeah, you could come visit us in Dejvice.

536
00:25:28,550 --> 00:25:30,750
Look, Kvetos, rather not, okay?

537
00:25:32,550 --> 00:25:34,750
What, me, bragging?

538
00:25:35,450 --> 00:25:36,750
Fine then, come visit.

539
00:25:37,050 --> 00:25:38,850
Sure, anytime, Saturday.

540
00:25:38,920 --> 00:25:39,480
Sure.

541
00:25:39,950 --> 00:25:41,950
Take care, bye.

542
00:25:48,750 --> 00:25:49,990
What an idiot.

543
00:25:51,550 --> 00:25:53,150
Don't count on Xenie.
